Title: Quantum Field Theory without Divergences

Authors: G. H. Gadiyar

Comments: (Latex file 9 pages) e-mail

A fundamental length is introduced into physics in a way which respects theprinciples of relativity and quantum field theory. This improves the propertiesalso indicated. When the fundamental length tends to zero the present versionof quantum field theory is recovered.